OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMan given year to live     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcancer-free after drug     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ftrial                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A man who "jumped at the chance" to    
OL,6, join a drug trial after being diagnosed
OL,7, with cancer and given 12 months to live
OL,8, has said "getting the all-clear was    
OL,9, overwhelming".                         
OL,11,FRobert Glynn was diagnosed with a form 
OL,12,Fof bile duct cancer in 2020 after going
OL,13,Fto the GP with severe shoulder pain.   
OL,15,FHe went on to join an immunotherapy    
OL,16,Ftrial at Manchester's The Christie.    
OL,18,FThe 51-year-old from Worsley, Salford, 
OL,19,Fsaid he was "very lucky as I had the   
OL,20,Fcancer for two years and had no idea". 
